The paper focuses on the verification of software for robotic assistants in human-robot interaction tasks, which falls under the scope of robotics (cs.RO). The use of belief-desire-intention (BDI) agents and artificial intelligence for test generation suggests a focus on AI (cs.AI) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The implementation of an automated testbench and the discovery of design issues suggest a focus on software engineering (cs.SE) and systems and control (cs.SY).
